oard.com/uderthommain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Der Thommain</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>New to the block</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>4/20/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>11:53:02 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">White agaisnt white the bear lifts her head. Famaliar sents and voices are on the fridge wind. She turns and moves closer to get a better look. <br>
<br>
Looking down form the hill she sees a small warrioress in blue shaking a rather beleagered woodsman. She blinks her small black eyes and makes out the familiar forms of those she knows well and those she has met only once before.<br>
<br>
Now what would those poor creatures from the summerlands be doing in this winterwasteland?  She move slowly not to be seen.  As yet she does not know if they need or want her aide as Febreeza is want to be very indepentant.  She starts to move on, but remembers Feb's knack for geting in over her head.  She decides to keep an eye on the travelers to see if they reach their destination without event or if her aid will be needed.  <br>
<br>
</font><P>DerThommain Breathnach
55 Luminary Final Destiny 
<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#383838><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Elder</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>4/27/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>8:16:21 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.honestevil.com/deleted_roster/hail_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Completely distracted in the realization that her cousin, Kristav, was here before her, Casidy did not see Crydee slip off into the distance.<br>
<br>
Taking her cousin by the hand and helping warm him up, she noticed a strong smell of honey mead lingering on his breath. <br>
<br>
"Awe cuz, I suppose you didn't save me a bit o the mead did ye?" Casidy mockingly chided Kristav.<br>
<br>
With a smile and a twinkle Kristav brought out a flask and presented it to Casidy. "A token from home," Kristav replied, knowing full well that nothing could bring the sort of smile that honey mead could to Casidy’s face.<br>
<br>
"I seem to recall there was a note that was to go along with your arrival, and hopefully you have the map for where this adventure will lead us" Casidy looked hopefully at the wide eyed bard.<br>
<br>
Why they had chosen Kristav to be the messenger, Casidy could only guess. His youth showed vividly about him, he was many seasons younger than Casidy. Truth be told, he had just begun to study the flute, and had many lessons ahead.<br>
<br>
Perhaps this was a test for her, she thought briefly, to ensure his safety throughout the passage. It wouldn't be the first time the guild had send her a young bard to tutor.<br>
<br>
Well, she would take this into consideration. Kristav was after all, an able-bodied swords man. He should be as capable to hold his weapons, and his mead as well as many within the party.<br>
<br>
Kristav turned and began to rummage through his pockets. "Yes, there was a note here... somewhere... " He continued looking, becoming more frantic with each passing moment.<br>
<br>
Jzonn, and Febreeza were just outside of the covering, speaking to the druid. She seemed familiar at this range, but Casidy could not be certain of whom she was at this distance, only that she was an elf, a wood elf, and the large staff gave her away as likely a druid.<br>
<br>
Taino looked on, pretending to busy himself with tending the fire, as Casidy began to help Kristav go through his satchel, looking for some document with the symbol of the Antonican Bard Guild seal upon it.<br>
<br>
<br>
