~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#383838><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Boardfellow</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>4/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>4:49:57 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">With a sigh Cuthbert kept his eye on the young bard, this coming at the request of Casidy's Mother. How Cuthbert wanted to return to adventuring himself even though there just is not much left to see, Cuthbert had no intentions of being retired to head up some Bard guild somewhere and was a bit tired of planning defense strategies with King Tormax. <br>
<br>
Now here he was babysitting some a young bard and her friends. The mother had said that Casidy also had some information for him that he might find useful should he care to introduce himself to her. As a master of lore, Cuthbert was curious as to what this young bard could offer him in the way of information. His Bardic vanity was making it very tough for him to even consider this as a reality. Cuthbert felt he owed the mother after that night in Qeynos. The least Cuthbert could have done was to leave her a note or say good bye, but such is the life of a musician. <br>
<br>
Looking at his provisions, Cuthbert looked at the sky and sighed wishing that this group moved a bit faster through their journey. Although trying to be honest with himself, Cuthbert tried to determine if his judgement of the was harsh because he wanted to check out some rumors in Western Wastes or if they really were a tad slow moving. <br>
<br>
It was at that time Cuthbert decided to use and ancient song to lull the young group to sleep and went up behind Casidy under the guise of Selo's Song of Travel and said, Hello.....</font><P>Cuthbert Dirgewielder <BR>El Virtuoso and Uber Geek of F.U.<P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0> at: 4/30/01 5:17:15 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#383838><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Elder</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>5/8/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ff0000>9:13:01 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.honestevil.com/deleted_roster/hail_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Casidy heard the sounds as they whispered in her ear...<br>
<br>
She was listening intently to place the song... she had heard this before.... she did not notice her companions one by one fall off to a fitful sleep.<br>
<br>
She did however notice the melody change, to a more familiar sound.<br>
<br>
Selo's song of travel was a tune she had heard many times before.... but who was this bard, shrouding himself from her view....<br>
<br>
Just as Casidy was beginning to wonder, he said, hello...<br>
<br>
Casidy turned, and noticed her companions all asleep before her.<br>
<br>
Scowling softly back to the, still invisible bard, Casidy spoke over sharply "There might have been a better way to gather my attentions then to force my friends to slumber..."<br>
<br>
Realizing she had been a bit harsh, Casidy sighed "You have my attentions, perhaps we should step off a bit and talk?"<br>
<br>
The bard agreed, and the two of them headed down to the edge of the waterline a bit off from the camp.<br>
<br>
Her friends would awaken in a few moments, with a slight ringing to their heads, and find themselves missing one Casidy.<br>
<br>
The bard at her side, quickly shrouded Casidy within his song, and the two headed off to the waters edge.<br>
<br>
Now that the man was visible, Casidy smiled to herself. She well, recognized this bard. <br>
<br>
Casidy had been raised in Kelethin, by her mother, and the man that had adopted her as his daughter. Casidy had never before met her true father, but her mother had told her many tales, and managed to keep up on his travels throughout the land. This bard before her, was her father.<br>
<br>
Smiling smugly to herself, Casidy carefully considered whether to reveal this information to him. In her travels, she had heard many tales of her fathers outings, and many of the adventures he had were notorious. Through all these adventures and all his travels, little did he know that he had a daughter growing and learning with his gift for song.<br>
<br>
"So, Master Cuthbert, what brings you to this icy wasteland?" Casidy smiled in her overly charming way "And how may this wee bard assist you in your travels?"<br>
<br>
